correctness.rationale: Major factual errors and multiple schema violations. Key issues: (1) ALD method set to PEALD, but article uses photo-ALD with UV lamp (no plasma); should be TALD per allowed enum. Also 'plasmaPower' is None (schema expects object if present) and should be omitted when no plasma. (2) supercycleDesign is None (invalid type; optional object should be omitted). (3) Dosing/purge times incorrectly recorded as 2 ms and 8 ms; article states 2 s and 8 s. If schema requires MilliSEC, values should be 2000 ms and 8000 ms. (4) GrowthPerCycle 1 Å and numberOfCycles 200 are not supported by the text and are inconsistent with the 200 nm thickness (implies ~10 Å/cycle). (5) Flow rates, nucleationPeriod, and purgingGas assignment are not reported and appear fabricated. (6) Electrical properties: resistivity misconverted—article reports 6.9×10^-4 Ω·cm; correct OHM-M value is 6.9×10^-6 Ω·m, not 6.9×10^-4 Ω·m. Carrier density reported as 3.9×10^20 per m^3 but article gives 3.9×10^20 cm^-3; correct SI is 3.9×10^26 m^-3. Mobility 57.3 cm^2/V·s is cited for prior photo-MOCVD films, not the present photo-ALD films. (7) OpticalProperties subfields set to None (schema expects objects if present); also misses reported ~85% transmittance. (8) Uniformity, conformality, filmComposition (99.9% and 1:1 by XPS), roughness (AFM 5 nm), and filmDensity (XRR 5.6 g/dm^3) are not in the article and are likely fabricated. (9) DeviceProperties (field-effect mobility, threshold voltage, SS, on/off, device structure) are not reported anywhere in the article—fabricated. (10) Additional None/"Not Found" placeholders risk schema non-compliance and lack traceability. Correct or remove: aldMethod (use TALD), remove plasmaPower and supercycleDesign, fix dosing/purge time units, remove unsupported GPC/numberOfCycles/flowRates/nucleationPeriod, correct resistivity and carrier density units, remove mobility if not reported, remove fabricated material/device properties, and avoid None values to meet schema.

completeness.rationale: The extraction is largely incomplete and contains multiple factual and schema issues. Key problems: (1) ALD method misidentified as PEALD; the article reports photo-ALD (UV-assisted, non-plasma). A second, separate thermal ALD process described for comparison (ALD vs photo-ALD in Figs. 2 and 5) is missing. (2) Schema violations/placeholders: plasmaPower is null (should be omitted if not PEALD), supercycleDesign is null, and several optical properties are set to null; reactor name/manufacturer and deliveryMethod are filled with “Not Found.” (3) Dosing/purge times: article gives 2 s and 8 s; extraction uses MilliSEC units but numeric values 2.0 and 8.0 (should be 2000 ms and 8000 ms). (4) Unsubstantiated or invented process values: growth-per-cycle (1 Å), number of cycles (200), nucleation period (5 cycles), flow rates (50/100 sccm) are not reported. (5) Material properties: resistivity unit conversion is wrong (reported 6.9×10^-4 Ω·cm should be 6.9×10^-6 Ω·m, not 6.9×10^-4 Ω·m); carrier density unit conversion is wrong (3.9×10^20 cm^-3 should be 3.9×10^26 m^-3); mobility 57.3 cm^2/Vs is from prior photo-MOCVD work, not this study; uniformity %, conformality aspect ratio, XPS composition/ratio, AFM roughness, and XRR density are not in the article. (6) DeviceProperties (TFT metrics) are not reported in the paper and should not be populated. Items to add/review: correct ALD method and remove plasma-related fields; add a separate thermal ALD process if data are extracted; fix dosing/purge time units; remove unsupported flow rates, GPC, cycles, nucleation; correct resistivity and carrier density units; remove unreported optical/film composition/roughness/density/device metrics or supply grounded values; keep supported items (substrate, precursors, co-reactant, Ar carrier/purge, pressure≈0.1 Torr, film thickness ≈200 nm, saturation true, crystallinity from XRD).
